Scan recorded sessions for secrets (docs/redaction.md).

Reports what was detected (type, step, location, correlation tag) — never the secret itself. Exits 4 when findings exist, so CI can gate on a clean scan; 0 when clean.

Usage: hh scan [OPTIONS] [SESSION]

Arguments:
  [SESSION]
          Session short id, full id, or `last`. Defaults to `last` (or use --all)

Options:
      --all
          Scan every recorded session

      --json
          Emit machine-readable JSON instead of a table

  -h, --help
          Print help (see a summary with '-h')

Example:
  hh scan last
  hh scan a1b2c3 --json
  hh scan --all
